<recipe>
  <name>Monkey Bread (formerly "Monkey Break")</name>
  <yield_count>12</yield_count>
  <yield_measure>servings</yield_measure>
  <notes>Sadly no monkey is included in monkey bread</notes>
  <ingredients>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>1 cup</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>milk</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>2 pkg</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>dry yeast</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>4 tbsp</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>sugar</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>1 tsp</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>salt</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>1/2 cup</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>melted butter</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>3 1/2 cup</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>sifted flour</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>1 egg</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>slightly beaten</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>1/4 cup</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>additional butter</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>1/4 cup</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>oil</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
  </ingredients>
  <preparation>Scald milk and allow to cool to lukewarm.  Dissolve yeast in scalded milk in a large bowl.  Beat in sugar, salt, butter, flour and egg.

Let double in a warm place and punch down.  On a floured board, roll dough out to 1/4".  Cut in diamond pattern 2 1/2 inches apart.

Dip each piece in a mixture of cooking oil and butter.  Arrange in a a 9-inch ring mold and let rise until almost double.  Bake 400F for 30 minutes or until golden brown.  Pull apart to serve.</preparation>
